I use Emacs because I like experimenting with languages like Erlang, Haskell and Ruby,
and I've found there is practically always a Emacs mode for any language which is at least comparable to a dedicated IDE (which may not exist) and for which I don't need to learn a whole new set of key bindings.

Blog (in Russian): http://alexey-rom.livejournal.com/

My Emacs Starter Kit fork: http://github.com/alexeyr/emacs-starter-kit

A functional programming library for C#: http://code.google.com/p/functional-dotnet/

